                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, March 2: India has relaxed the ban on import of toys from China on the condition that it conforms to global safety standards. There were fears that the ban might not stand the scrutiny of the disputes panel if Beijing took up the issue with the World Trade Organization. The government has notified that import of Chinese toys will be allowed only if it conformed to stringent US standards. The government had imposed the ban in January for six months. According to government notification, manufacturers have to certify that import consignments are tested by an independent laboratory accredited by the International Laboratory Accreditation Cooperation.                            
	 Geneva, March 2: Tata Motors will unveil the European version of small car Nano tomorrow at the Geneva Motor Show. The auto maker is gearing up for the commercial launch of Nano in India this month. According to industry sources, the company will showcase the car at the Geneva Motor Show.                                                                                                                           
